BFN 

  [Excerpts] The fifth Arab Energy Conference began in Cairo 
today. Arab oil and energy ministers, in addition to the 
ministers of electricity in the five countries to be linked by a 
single grid, are participating. These countries are Syria, 
Egypt, Jordan, Iraq, and Turkey. [passage omitted] 
  In a speech he delivered for Syria, Dr. Nadir al-Nabulis, 
minister of oil and mineral resources, said Syria under 
President Hafiz al-Asad has succeeded in establishing a 
developed economy and has attained many achievements in the oil 
and natural gas industry. [passage omitted] 
  Dr. al-Nabulsi said that the imposition of taxes on oil on 
the pretext of the safety of the environment is not based on 
clear scientific foundations. [passage omitted] 

